00:13:21.260 --> 00:13:23.650 align:middle line:84%
I talked to shareholders
from these companies.

00:13:23.650 --> 00:13:25.595 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't be happier
with the results.

00:13:25.595 --> 00:13:26.470 align:middle line:90%
So there you have it.

00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:31.547 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, let's talk about some
more specifics, such as how

00:13:31.547 --> 00:13:32.380 align:middle line:90%
about The Body Shop?

00:13:32.380 --> 00:13:34.940 align:middle line:84%
This is a company most
everybody's familiar with.

00:13:34.940 --> 00:13:36.550 align:middle line:84%
>>This is another
company that I got

00:13:36.550 --> 00:13:40.610 align:middle line:84%
sort of criticized
for including.

00:13:40.610 --> 00:13:43.360 align:middle line:84%
The Body Shop is a
controversial company.

00:13:43.360 --> 00:13:45.080 align:middle line:84%
And the reason
they're controversial

00:13:45.080 --> 00:13:48.880 align:middle line:84%
is that people criticize them
of not putting their money where

00:13:48.880 --> 00:13:50.430 align:middle line:90%
their mouth is.

00:13:50.430 --> 00:13:52.400 align:middle line:84%
And the reason
they're criticized

00:13:52.400 --> 00:13:54.540 align:middle line:84%
for not putting their
money where their mouth is

00:13:54.540 --> 00:13:57.990 align:middle line:84%
is because when Anita
Roddick founded that company,

00:13:57.990 --> 00:14:02.350 align:middle line:84%
she decided to make it a
model for corporate justice.

00:14:02.350 --> 00:14:05.050 align:middle line:84%
So what she did,
instead of just creating

00:14:05.050 --> 00:14:09.420 align:middle line:84%
a company that behaves well, was
put pressure on other companies

00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:10.149 align:middle line:90%
to behave well.

00:14:10.149 --> 00:14:12.690 align:middle line:84%
And let me tell you, she made
a lot of enemies by doing that.

00:14:12.690 --> 00:14:17.050 align:middle line:84%
She would go into
Nigeria and protest

00:14:17.050 --> 00:14:22.320 align:middle line:84%
the actions of oil and chemical
companies that were operating,

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:25.685 align:middle line:84%
based on human rights and
environmental violations

00:14:25.685 --> 00:14:27.440 align:middle line:90%
and sins against humanity.

00:14:27.440 --> 00:14:30.750 align:middle line:84%
She really made those
violations known to the public

00:14:30.750 --> 00:14:34.050 align:middle line:84%
at a time when people
weren't really watching

00:14:34.050 --> 00:14:36.770 align:middle line:84%
what corporations were doing
in the third world countries

00:14:36.770 --> 00:14:38.292 align:middle line:84%
and developing
nations they entered.

00:14:38.292 --> 00:14:39.500 align:middle line:90%
They weren't really watching.

00:14:39.500 --> 00:14:41.580 align:middle line:84%
These companies don't
have the obligation

00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:43.527 align:middle line:84%
to report to shareholders
and the public

00:14:43.527 --> 00:14:45.110 align:middle line:84%
what they're doing
in these countries.

00:14:45.110 --> 00:14:47.775 align:middle line:90%
So she became very unpopular.

00:14:47.775 --> 00:14:50.070 align:middle line:84%
She made a lot of
friends in high places,

00:14:50.070 --> 00:14:51.980 align:middle line:84%
but made a lot of
enemies in high places.

00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:57.310 align:middle line:84%
Since then, the company
had some difficulty,

00:14:57.310 --> 00:15:00.700 align:middle line:84%
in the sense that it promised
to do a lot of things.

00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Then it went public,
and it had difficulty

00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:05.500 align:middle line:84%
delivering on some
of those promises.

00:15:05.500 --> 00:15:09.940 align:middle line:84%
However, it succeeded in
delivering on many others.

00:15:09.940 --> 00:15:13.370 align:middle line:84%
And so I focused on what
they've succeeded in doing.

00:15:13.370 --> 00:15:18.270 align:middle line:84%
They've literally freed
prisoners of conscience.

00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:23.860 align:middle line:84%
They've helped several prisoners
escape death sentences.

00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:26.900 align:middle line:84%
These were prisoners that were
being held in developing areas

00:15:26.900 --> 00:15:31.640 align:middle line:84%
for protesting against corporate
activities in those areas.

00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:32.890 align:middle line:90%
So it's incredible.

00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:35.920 align:middle line:84%
So they've done a great deal
for the human rights cause.

00:15:35.920 --> 00:15:40.040 align:middle line:84%
They've activated two
million people actually

00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:43.120 align:middle line:84%
through a human rights
campaign they did.

00:15:43.120 --> 00:15:44.150 align:middle line:90%
And so it's incredible.

00:15:44.150 --> 00:15:45.730 align:middle line:90%
So they've had a huge reach.

00:15:45.730 --> 00:15:49.300 align:middle line:84%
They've also really changed
the law on animal testing

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:50.610 align:middle line:90%
in the UK.

00:15:50.610 --> 00:15:53.350 align:middle line:84%
They've also done a great
deal for women's rights.

00:15:53.350 --> 00:15:56.337 align:middle line:84%
They've also done a great deal
for a host of other issues.

00:15:56.337 --> 00:15:57.920 align:middle line:84%
Domestic violence
is something they're

00:15:57.920 --> 00:15:59.940 align:middle line:90%
very focused on right now.

00:15:59.940 --> 00:16:03.270 align:middle line:84%
So this is a company that
has done tremendous things.

00:16:03.270 --> 00:16:04.820 align:middle line:84%
But those tremendous
things have been

00:16:04.820 --> 00:16:06.850 align:middle line:90%
overshadowed by controversy.

00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:10.430 align:middle line:84%
So it was my objective
to go in and go, uhuh.

00:16:10.430 --> 00:16:12.590 align:middle line:84%
We're not hearing
the whole story.

00:16:12.590 --> 00:16:16.110 align:middle line:84%
What we hear is, oh, The Body
Shop, they're controversial.

00:16:16.110 --> 00:16:17.826 align:middle line:90%
Stay away from them.

00:16:17.826 --> 00:16:18.950 align:middle line:90%
They don't walk their talk.

00:16:18.950 --> 00:16:21.360 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually there's
evidence that they do.

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:23.800 align:middle line:84%
There's a great deal of
evidence that they do.

00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:26.720 align:middle line:84%
And so I wanted to tell their
story, and I'm glad I did.

00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>>What was her original
mission statement?

00:16:29.940 --> 00:16:33.100 align:middle line:84%
