That's a very important thing.

00:21:17.290 --> 00:21:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>>This brings up a
very large topic.

00:21:21.440 --> 00:21:25.370 align:middle line:84%
It's endemic to the natural food
industry now that companies--

00:21:25.370 --> 00:21:27.940 align:middle line:90%
I won't name names.

00:21:27.940 --> 00:21:30.670 align:middle line:84%
This is not designed to
make anyone look bad.

00:21:30.670 --> 00:21:33.315 align:middle line:90%
>>Let me name names.

00:21:33.315 --> 00:21:36.130 align:middle line:84%
>>Large corporations
are taking over

00:21:36.130 --> 00:21:40.430 align:middle line:84%
these beautiful little organic
and natural food companies.

00:21:40.430 --> 00:21:40.930 align:middle line:90%
>>I know.

00:21:40.930 --> 00:21:42.460 align:middle line:90%
It happened to Odwalla.

00:21:42.460 --> 00:21:45.400 align:middle line:84%
>>And for decades
literally to grow.

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:48.170 align:middle line:84%
And then finally, it's
time for our payoff.

00:21:48.170 --> 00:21:50.915 align:middle line:84%
We have been working our
tails off for 20 years

00:21:50.915 --> 00:21:52.290 align:middle line:84%
to get this thing
up and running.

00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:54.520 align:middle line:84%
It's attracted the
money and attention.

00:21:54.520 --> 00:21:57.150 align:middle line:84%
And like you say,
the deal usually

00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:59.320 align:middle line:90%
isn't structured in such a way.

00:21:59.320 --> 00:22:01.690 align:middle line:84%
So the consumer is often
duped into thinking

00:22:01.690 --> 00:22:05.405 align:middle line:84%
that they are supporting
a natural food company,

00:22:05.405 --> 00:22:10.291 align:middle line:84%
when in fact it might be Disney
Corp. or M&M Mars bars or--

00:22:10.291 --> 00:22:11.790 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, there are
a couple of things

00:22:11.790 --> 00:22:12.915 align:middle line:90%
that I have say about that.

00:22:12.915 --> 00:22:15.360 align:middle line:84%
First of all, I
think it's terrific

00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:19.290 align:middle line:84%
that M&M Mars Corp.
or Disney owns

00:22:19.290 --> 00:22:22.239 align:middle line:84%
a small, little, precious
company because that means

00:22:22.239 --> 00:22:23.780 align:middle line:84%
they're going in
the right direction.

00:22:23.780 --> 00:22:25.613 align:middle line:84%
That means they're
investing in a trend that

00:22:25.613 --> 00:22:29.980 align:middle line:84%
is the most important business
trend, I think, in existence.

00:22:29.980 --> 00:22:32.260 align:middle line:84%
That is so positive
for this movement.

00:22:32.260 --> 00:22:34.950 align:middle line:84%
I hope that that
happens more often.

00:22:34.950 --> 00:22:38.870 align:middle line:84%
Having said that,
it is very typical

00:22:38.870 --> 00:22:40.650 align:middle line:84%
that when a company
is taken over,

00:22:40.650 --> 00:22:42.910 align:middle line:90%
its senior staff is replaced.

00:22:42.910 --> 00:22:44.510 align:middle line:90%
It happened at Ben and Jerry's.

00:22:44.510 --> 00:22:46.310 align:middle line:84%
It's happened to a
lot of companies.

00:22:46.310 --> 00:22:48.720 align:middle line:84%
Ben and Jerry's was
taken over by Unilever,

00:22:48.720 --> 00:22:50.260 align:middle line:90%
and Ben Cohen left.

00:22:50.260 --> 00:22:53.116 align:middle line:84%
And actually the
CEO was replaced.

00:22:53.116 --> 00:22:54.240 align:middle line:90%
So management was replaced.

00:22:54.240 --> 00:22:57.400 align:middle line:84%
So basically what happens
in an acquisition,

00:22:57.400 --> 00:22:59.220 align:middle line:84%
and it's up to the
lawyers, and it's

00:22:59.220 --> 00:23:01.870 align:middle line:84%
up to the owners of the company
to sort of grapple this out.

00:23:01.870 --> 00:23:04.340 align:middle line:84%
But oftentimes,
you lose control.

00:23:04.340 --> 00:23:09.620 align:middle line:84%
And when that happens,
operations change.

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:11.780 align:middle line:90%
And that's a negative trend.

00:23:11.780 --> 00:23:14.490 align:middle line:84%
See, because what these big
corporations don't realize

00:23:14.490 --> 00:23:16.100 align:middle line:84%
is that the reason
the company is

00:23:16.100 --> 00:23:20.590 align:middle line:84%
so valuable in the first place
and an attractive acquisition

00:23:20.590 --> 00:23:23.220 align:middle line:84%
is not just because
of its brand identity.

00:23:23.220 --> 00:23:27.460 align:middle line:84%
Its brand identity is driven
by a business philosophy.

00:23:27.460 --> 00:23:30.980 align:middle line:84%
Now, when you change the
core, the brand image

00:23:30.980 --> 00:23:32.780 align:middle line:90%
is gonna catch up.

00:23:32.780 --> 00:23:35.060 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to see
changes in the marketplace.

00:23:35.060 --> 00:23:36.210 align:middle line:90%
And that's happened.

00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:40.800 align:middle line:84%
It's happened with Ben
and Jerry's sort of.

00:23:40.800 --> 00:23:42.189 align:middle line:90%
They're doing extremely well.

00:23:42.189 --> 00:23:43.980 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, a lot of
people are going, gee,

00:23:43.980 --> 00:23:45.021 align:middle line:90%
are they going to change?

00:23:45.021 --> 00:23:47.810 align:middle line:90%


00:23:47.810 --> 00:23:53.280 align:middle line:84%
How is Unilever going to
handle the social, the sort

00:23:53.280 --> 00:23:55.130 align:middle line:84%
of soulful aspects
of the company?

00:23:55.130 --> 00:23:56.640 align:middle line:90%
Will that go away?

00:23:56.640 --> 00:23:59.242 align:middle line:84%
And so people are
still watching to see

00:23:59.242 --> 00:24:00.950 align:middle line:84%
what's going to happen
with that company.

00:24:00.950 --> 00:24:02.930 align:middle line:84%
I think it will be very
interesting to watch.

00:24:02.930 --> 00:24:04.960 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they've done
a reasonably good job.

00:24:04.960 --> 00:24:06.480 align:middle line:90%
I have to tip my hat to them.

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:10.360 align:middle line:84%
And I also have to say that,
when a company like Starbucks,

00:24:10.360 --> 00:24:12.370 align:middle line:90%
a different example.

00:24:12.370 --> 00:24:18.220 align:middle line:84%
Even if Starbucks only offers 5%
of its total coffee assortment

00:24:18.220 --> 00:24:22.120 align:middle line:84%
as fair trade, that
makes a huge impact

00:24:22.120 --> 00:24:24.390 align:middle line:90%
because of Starbucks' power.

00:24:24.390 --> 00:24:27.050 align:middle line:84%
So that's actually, I think
it's a positive trend, not

00:24:27.050 --> 00:24:29.049 align:middle line:84%
a negative trend,
that big business is

00:24:29.049 --> 00:24:30.090 align:middle line:90%
getting involved in this.

00:24:30.090 --> 00:24:33.090 align:middle line:84%
I hope more big businesses
get involved in this.

00:24:33.090 --> 00:24:35.680 align:middle line:84%
>>Are you beginning to see
a shift in the philosophy

00:24:35.680 --> 00:24:38.290 align:middle line:84%
where it's not, as
you said earlier, just

00:24:38.290 --> 00:24:41.100 align:middle line:84%
to cash in on a
developed brand name,

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:44.450 align:middle line:84%
but really maybe a
new type of leadership

00:24:44.450 --> 00:24:46.330 align:middle line:84%
emerging that's
looking to carry forth

00:24:46.330 --> 00:24:50.290 align:middle line:84%
the original soul, the
intent of the company?

00:24:50.290 --> 00:24:52.450 align:middle line:90%
>>Yes, absolutely.

00:24:52.450 --> 00:24:55.000 align:middle line:84%
I think that more companies
are waking up to the fact

00:24:55.000 --> 00:25:00.000 align:middle line:84%
that this is more than just a
superficial image-based trend.

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:01.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's what it's
criticized, and how

00:25:01.930 --> 00:25:03.930 align:middle line:84%
it's characterized
by a lot of people.

00:25:03.930 --> 00:25:05.890 align:middle line:90%
That's not the case.

00:25:05.890 --> 00:25:09.660 align:middle line:84%
Because what's going on is
in the system of capitalism

00:25:09.660 --> 00:25:10.880 align:middle line:90%
there are two trends.

00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:15.670 align:middle line:84%
First, you have an
increased demand for--

00:25:15.670 --> 00:25:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And people are
really watching out

00:25:17.930 --> 00:25:19.360 align:middle line:84%
for errors of
corporate judgment.

00:25:19.360 --> 00:25:22.240 align:middle line:84%
It's becoming a lot harder
to get away with wrongdoing.

00:25:22.240 --> 00:25:23.570 align:middle line:90%
And people are demanding more.

00:25:23.570 --> 00:25:26.400 align:middle line:84%
When I say people, I mean
shareholders, consumers,

00:25:26.400 --> 00:25:30.090 align:middle line:84%
the press are demanding
more from companies in terms

00:25:30.090 --> 00:25:33.550 align:middle line:84%
of integrity, transparency,
responsibility.

00:25:33.550 --> 00:25:35.880 align:middle line:84%
They're demanding
a lot more today

00:25:35.880 --> 00:25:37.090 align:middle line:90%
than they did 10 years ago.

00:25:37.090 --> 00:25:38.310 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:25:38.310 --> 00:25:40.150 align:middle line:84%
That's a demand in
the marketplace.

00:25:40.150 --> 00:25:44.580 align:middle line:84%
So supply and demand,
companies have to address that.

00:25:44.580 --> 00:25:49.995 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, you have
companies like Stonyfield, HP,

00:25:49.995 --> 00:25:52.570 align:middle line:84%
a huge slew of companies
that are putting

00:25:52.570 --> 00:25:55.620 align:middle line:84%
their values into
action, that are behaving

00:25:55.620 --> 00:25:59.410 align:middle line:84%
in an ethical way, that are
transforming their behavior

00:25:59.410 --> 00:26:01.900 align:middle line:90%
and profiting from that.

00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:05.170 align:middle line:84%
They are outperforming their
competitors in the marketplace.

00:26:05.170 --> 00:26:07.530 align:middle line:84%
So put those two
trends together,

00:26:07.530 --> 00:26:08.720 align:middle line:90%
and what does that say?

00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:12.110 align:middle line:90%


00:26:12.110 --> 00:26:16.460 align:middle line:84%
This is not an image-based,
superficial movement.

00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:19.172 align:middle line:84%
I mean I really think
this trend has legs.

00:26:19.172 --> 00:26:20.780 align:middle line:90%
>>Tell us the story of HP.

00:26:20.780 --> 00:26:23.260 align:middle line:84%
You just brushed past
them a moment ago.

00:26:23.260 --> 00:26:24.850 align:middle line:90%
>>Well, HP is interesting.

00:26:24.850 --> 00:26:27.510 align:middle line:84%
That is a company going through
some major transformation

00:26:27.510 --> 00:26:29.210 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:26:29.210 --> 00:26:33.060 align:middle line:84%
What people don't know is that
that's a company very heavily

00:26:33.060 --> 00:26:37.110 align:middle line:84%
invested in what's
called microcapitalism.

00:26:37.110 --> 00:26:40.280 align:middle line:84%
Microcapitalism is
about going into areas,

00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:44.040 align:middle line:84%
well for HP it's about
