00:27:00.470 --> 00:27:04.490 align:middle line:84%
in society, who have access to
all these great technologies,

00:27:04.490 --> 00:27:09.610 align:middle line:84%
from poorer people, who have
no access to any technology.

00:27:09.610 --> 00:27:13.290 align:middle line:84%
So that gap is getting
bigger and bigger

00:27:13.290 --> 00:27:14.930 align:middle line:90%
as technology advances.

00:27:14.930 --> 00:27:16.910 align:middle line:84%
So they have gone
into these areas,

00:27:16.910 --> 00:27:19.910 align:middle line:84%
like Kuppam, India, South
Africa, South America,

00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:20.990 align:middle line:90%
all over the place.

00:27:20.990 --> 00:27:23.470 align:middle line:84%
And they have
engineered technology

00:27:23.470 --> 00:27:25.440 align:middle line:84%
that meets the needs
of the local people.

00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:28.890 align:middle line:84%
They've enabled those people
to join the global economy,

00:27:28.890 --> 00:27:32.120 align:middle line:84%
to become entrepreneurs,
to raise themselves

00:27:32.120 --> 00:27:33.240 align:middle line:90%
above the poverty line.

00:27:33.240 --> 00:27:34.739 align:middle line:84%
So it's not a charity
program, where

00:27:34.739 --> 00:27:36.060 align:middle line:90%
they are handing out money.

00:27:36.060 --> 00:27:39.930 align:middle line:84%
They're giving people the tools
to become self-sufficient.

00:27:39.930 --> 00:27:42.940 align:middle line:84%
In doing that, they're
expanding their global presence.

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:44.650 align:middle line:90%
So that's an interesting case.

00:27:44.650 --> 00:27:49.830 align:middle line:84%
It's an aspect of the company's
long term growth strategy.

00:27:49.830 --> 00:27:53.407 align:middle line:84%
>>The company, I always want
to say ebiza, but it's Eziba.

